# DDD Architecture Overview

Every business module in this codebase follows a strict four-layer structure. Layers only reference each other in one direction — inner layers never know about outer layers.

## Module Folder Structure

```
src/
└── <module>/                          ← One folder per Bounded Context
    ├── domain/                        ← Zero framework deps — pure TypeScript
    │   ├── aggregates/                ← Aggregate Roots (*.aggregate.ts)
    │   ├── entities/                  ← Child entities (*.entity.ts)
    │   ├── value-objects/             ← Immutable, equality by value (*.vo.ts)
    │   ├── events/                    ← Domain events, past tense (*.event.ts)
    │   ├── errors/                    ← Domain exceptions (*.error.ts)
    │   ├── services/                  ← Domain services, spans aggregates
    │   ├── repositories/              ← Interfaces only — no implementation
    │   ├── factories/                 ← Complex object creation (*.factory.ts)
    │   ├── policies/                  ← Business rules / specs (*.policy.ts)
    │   ├── enums/                     ← Domain enumerations (*.enum.ts)
    │   └── ports/                     ← External service interfaces (*.port.ts)
    ├── application/                   ← Orchestration — handlers, use-cases, services
    ├── infrastructure/                ← DB, ORM, HTTP adapters — concrete implementations
    └── presentation/                  ← Controllers, DTOs, guards — HTTP edge
```

## Dependency Direction (enforce strictly)

```
Presentation  →  Application  →  Domain  ✅
Infrastructure               →  Domain  ✅
Application   →  Infrastructure  via interface tokens only ✅

Domain  →  Application      ❌
Domain  →  Infrastructure   ❌
Domain  →  Presentation     ❌
```

The domain layer must have **zero** `@nestjs/*` or Prisma imports.
The only permitted exception is `BusinessError` which extends `Error` (see domain layer rule).

## Layer Responsibilities at a Glance

| Layer | Allowed imports | Must NOT import |
|---|---|---|
| `domain/` | Pure TypeScript, `@lib/core` models | `@nestjs/*`, Prisma, HTTP, DB |
| `application/` | Domain interfaces/events, `@nestjs/*` DI | Prisma, HTTP response types |
| `infrastructure/` | Prisma, domain interfaces | HTTP, presentation types |
| `presentation/` | Application services, DTOs, `@nestjs/*` | Prisma, domain internals |

## Quick Checklist for a New Feature

- [ ] Aggregate in `domain/aggregates/` extends `AggregateRoot<T>` with `#` private fields
- [ ] Static `create(...)` factory — no `new` called from outside the domain
- [ ] Every state-changing method: invariant guard → mutate → `touch()` → `addDomainEvent(...)`
- [ ] Invariant violations throw a typed error extending `BusinessError` from `domain/errors/`
- [ ] Child entities in `domain/entities/` extend `BaseDomain<T>` — no repository, no events
- [ ] Value objects in `domain/value-objects/` are immutable, no `id`, equality by value
- [ ] Domain events in `domain/events/` extend `DomainEvent`, past-tense names, one per method
- [ ] Repository interface in `domain/repositories/` — `Symbol` token = interface name, extends `IRepository<T,ID,F>`
- [ ] External service contracts in `domain/ports/` — interface only, implemented in infrastructure
- [ ] Business rules in `domain/policies/` — pure, testable, no I/O
- [ ] Application handlers (`application/handler/`) inject via token, never import Prisma
- [ ] Prisma repository in `infrastructure/persistence/` implements the domain interface
- [ ] All five mapping hooks implemented (`toDomain`, `toCreateInput`, `toUpdateInput`, `toUniqueWhere`, `toFilterWhere`)
- [ ] `supportsSoftDelete()` overridden if the model has a `deletedAt` column

## Post-Implementation Validation (MANDATORY)

After **every** implementation — no exceptions — run these three gates in order:

```powershell
# 1. Type check — zero errors required
npx tsc --noEmit

# 2. Build — must succeed before shipping
npm run build

# 3. Tests — all must pass
npm test
```

**Rules:**
- Run all three even if earlier steps succeed — a passing typecheck does not guarantee a passing build.
- Do NOT consider the task done until all three commands exit with code `0`.
- If any command fails, fix the errors and re-run that command (and all subsequent ones) before marking the task complete.
- When Prisma models have changed, run `npm run generate:db` first, then the three gates above.
